description: Human Rights Watch accuses Kenyan authorities of not responding adequately to ongoing floods that have killed more than 170 people since the start of the rainy season.
title: As Kenya's flood toll rises, Human Rights Watch says officials must step up efforts

description: Indiana has its first competitive primary for governor in two decades, as six Republicans vie for their party's nomination. Current Governor Eric Holcomb is term-limited after eight years in office.
title: Indiana will have its first competitive primary election in two decades

description: Exxon Mobil's $60 billion deal to buy Pioneer Natural Resources received federal clearance, but former Pioneer CEO Scott Sheffield was barred from joining the new company's board of directors.
title: FTC bars former Pioneer CEO in Exxon Mobil deal, saying he colluded with OPEC

description: After months of delay in Congress, Ukraine is finally receiving the U.S. military aid it says is crucial in winning its fight against Russia. But after two years of war, what it means to win is increasingly complicated. We hear about the state of the conflict from our correspondent in Kyiv and our Pentagon correspondent.
title: What Does Winning Look Like for Ukraine Now?

description: Dean's family says he quickly fell into critical condition after being diagnosed with a MRSA bacterial infection. He is the second aviation whistleblower to die in the past three months.
title: Whistleblower Joshua Dean, who raised concerns about Boeing jets, dies at 45

description: Congress and President Biden say TikTok must shed its financial ties to China or face a ban in the U.S. But Washington Post tech reporter Drew Harwell says selling the company is complicated.
title: Why are so many government officials concerned about TikTok?

description: It's déjà vu for the luxury fitness company: Peloton is cutting about 400 more jobs, and its CEO is stepping down just two years after a major shakeup.
title: Peloton is laying off workers and replacing the CEO — again

description: Officially, only one person has caught the illness during the current outbreak. But with limited testing, cases could be flying under the radar.
title: The U.S. may be missing human cases of bird flu, scientists say

description: Law enforcement officers have moved into a pro-Palestinian encampment at UCLA. Arizona lawmakers voted to repeal a Civil War-era abortion ban.
title: Police enter UCLA anti-war encampment; Arizona repeals Civil War-era abortion ban

description: Workers are still removing pieces of the Key Bridge from Baltimore Harbor, but the fight over who will pay to replace it has already begun. Past accidents offer some clues about how it could play out.
title: Who will pay to replace Baltimore's Key Bridge? The legal battle has already begun

description: Federal regulators, medical experts and safe-sleep advocates have warned of the potential danger of weighted infant sleepwear, but manufacturers say their products have helped millions of families.
title: Amazon, Target and other retailers pull weighted infant sleepwear over safety fears

description: House Speaker Mike Johnson met with a group of Jewish students at Columbia University who say they've experienced antisemitic speech and harassment from protesters on and off campus.
title: House passes bill aimed to combat antisemitism amid college unrest

description: Former combat surgeons warn it won't be easy to restore medical readiness to where it was during the last war, much less where is needs to be for the next one.
title: After downsizing healthcare for years, Pentagon says medical readiness was a casualty

description: This year's winning entry is an emotional account of living with schizoaffective disorder, from a student at Miami Dade College.
title: College student explores rare mental health condition in award-winning podcast

title: Voters in this 'boomerang' county say they're nostalgic for the Trump economy

description: In a new report, Democrats are increasingly motivated by the issue of abortion - and increasingly supportive, as are independent voters. Republicans views have mostly remained the same.
title: As abortion looks like a key issue in 2024, voters more divided by party than ever

description: The maternal mortality rate in the U.S. in 2022 – while still high – went back to where it was before deaths surged during the height of the COVID-19 pandemic, according to the latest CDC report.
title: The CDC says maternal mortality rates in the U.S. got better, after a pandemic spike

description: In Wisconsin and Michigan, Donald Trump largely avoided the hush money trial that has mostly sidelined his campaign efforts as he tried to woo voters with a familiar speech in two major swing states.
title: Away from his New York trial, Donald Trump's campaign rallies are business as usual
